        <abstract>
            <p>Adaptations of orchid flowers. Believes the structure of all irregular flowers is adaptation to insect fertilisation.</p> 
<p><hi rend="italic">Linum grandiflorum</hi> distinguishes its own pollen so that when placed on stigma of same flower the pollen-tube is not even exserted.</p> 
